abstract: Prosecutors in Washington State announce that no criminal charges will be filed against three police officers involved in death of Antonio Zambrano-Montes in Pasco, farming community that is more than 50 percent Hispanic; death came during time of public scrutiny of police interaction with minorities, but prosecutors say investigation revealed no malice or criminal intent in officers' actions.
lead_paragraph: The death of Antonio Zambrano-Montes, 35, led to a wave of protests in Pasco, a farming community of 68,000 that is more the 50 percent Hispanic

headline.main: No Charges for Washington State Officers in Hispanic Man’s Death
headline.print_headline: 3 Officers Won’t Face Charges in Death of a Hispanic Man
